message.content: {"reasoning":"Ground truth: a stationary airplane is intersecting a wall (wing clipping) and, despite its propeller being stopped, is suspended above the ground (floating). Core symptoms: (1) wing-wall clipping, (2) aircraft appears parked yet hovers.\nGenerated report: describes a helicopter hovering unrealistically above a bridge (floating) and additionally points out an unrelated problem with the character’s water reflection. It does NOT mention any clipping with scenery or a stopped rotor/propeller; the only shared element is that an aircraft seems to float. Because the ground-truth bug specifically involves wall clipping and a non-rotating propeller, while the generated report lacks these details and introduces different issues (bridge context, reflection), they are not describing the same bug.","match":false}

{"reasoning":"Ground truth describes a specific clipping issue where the character’s hand penetrates their own body and comes out through the belly area. The generated report instead talks about non-standard character/weapon models, missing hands, and unusual floor textures, attributing this to possible modded content. It does not mention any hand-inside-body clipping or emergence from the belly. Hence, the core issues are different.","match":false}

{"reasoning":"Ground truth bug is about a sniper rifle floating in mid-air with its barrel clipping into a wall (positioning/physics/clipping issue). The generated report talks about wrong weapon colors and environmental texture artifacts; it does not mention floating, clipping, or weapon position. The issues described are completely different, so they do not match.","match":false}

{"reasoning":"Ground truth describes a clipping/intersection issue between a male character and a blue/cyan vehicle. The generated report talks about a texture glitch (black-and-white pattern) on the character’s clothing, with no mention of any vehicle or clipping. The problems (clipping vs. texture) and affected elements differ.","match":false}

{"reasoning":"Ground truth issue: the person (full body) is floating above the ground while kneeling. Generated report: only the character's white cloak is floating/detached, not the entire character. The described visual element and problem differ; no mention of the person themselves levitating. Therefore they do not describe the same bug.","match":false}

{"reasoning":"Ground truth bug: two characters are floating, their heads clip into ceiling. Key aspects: characters floating (not on ground) and clipping into geometry above.\nGenerated report: mainly about character shadow misalignment and unspecified objects floating in air. It does not mention characters themselves floating/clipping into ceiling; focuses on shadow rendering issue. \"Objects floating\" is vague and could be environment props, not characters, and no mention of head clipping. Therefore it does not clearly describe same bug.","match":false}

{"reasoning":"Ground truth bug: character's legs clip into (sink below) ground surface. Generated report: character appears floating above ground with no visible connection, implying being above terrain. These are opposite phenomena (sinking vs floating) and describe different visual issues. Therefore they do not match.","match":false}

{"reasoning":"Ground truth: body of front character is not rendered – only hand and gun are visible, giving the appearance that the gun is floating. Generated report: says the weapon is mis-aligned / floating and crosshair missing; does NOT mention that the character’s body is absent, instead attributes the problem to attachment/animation and adds a crosshair issue not in ground truth. Because the fundamental symptom in the ground truth is missing body rendering, which the generated report fails to identify, they are not describing the same bug.","match":false}

{"reasoning":"Ground truth: character standing next to a wall is frozen in an A-pose (arms out). \nGenerated report: character \"appears to be standing with their arms outstretched\" – i.e., an A-pose – and suggests a rendering/animation problem. Although it additionally mentions invisible hands/blue glow, the central observation (character is stuck in the default out-stretched pose due to an animation issue) aligns with the ground-truth issue. Location next to the wall and the added detail about missing hands are secondary and do not contradict the core symptom. Therefore, both describe the same bug.","match":true}

{"reasoning":"Ground truth bug concerns geometry clipping: parts of character (face and hand) intersecting a wall. Generated report describes lighting/shadow issue on character’s face (over-illumination). No mention of clipping or intersection with wall, and lighting is unrelated to geometry clipping. Therefore they do not describe the same bug.","match":false}

{"reasoning":"Ground truth bug is about character clipping into the wall (collision/positioning problem). Generated report talks about incorrect wooden texture tiling and lighting mismatch—entirely about rendering, not about character penetrating geometry. No overlap in core issue.","match":false}

{"reasoning":"Ground truth bug concerns the character’s anatomy: the head intersects the body and the neck is missing, indicating incorrect head placement. The generated report talks about clothing assets being misaligned (floating tie, coat not fitting), with no mention of head position, neck, or anatomy. The core issues are different—anatomy vs. clothing positioning—so they do not describe the same bug.","match":false}

{"reasoning":"The ground truth bug concerns two issues: (1) the flashlight’s beam is rendered as a hard-edged square patch instead of a smooth circular light and (2) a zombie character’s body is clipping through a table. The generated report, however, discusses unrelated problems: hair texture mixing, inconsistent face lighting, and a partially transparent weapon. None of the flashlight or body-clipping details are mentioned, and conversely, the ground truth does not mention hair or weapon transparency. Therefore, they describe different bugs.","match":false}

{"reasoning":"The ground truth bug highlights two specific issues: (1) a blue-gloved hand posed as if holding a gun even though no gun is shown, and (2) a character in a pink shirt whose head is clipping into the ground. The generated bug report instead talks about (1) character hands floating/not attached to the body, and (2) problems with Christmas-tree lighting and overall room lighting. It makes no mention of a gun-holding pose without a gun or of a head clipping into the ground, while it introduces lighting issues that are absent from the ground truth. Therefore, the generated report does not describe the same bug.","match":false}

{"reasoning":"The ground truth describes a physics/positioning bug: two cars intersecting (clipping) and a person floating on a car bonnet. The generated report talks about UI issues: incorrect health percentage, obscured name, extra button. No mention of cars, clipping, or floating character. Therefore they describe completely different issues.","match":false}

{"reasoning":"The ground truth bug concerns a character stuck in a default animation pose (A-pose/T-pose). The generated report talks about a building with a transparent roof, a weapon with a glowing 'U', and lighting/rendering issues. It makes no mention of the character’s pose or animation state. Likewise, the ground truth makes no mention of transparent roofs, glowing letters, or dark rendering. Therefore, the two describe completely different issues.","match":false}

{"reasoning":"The ground truth bug concerns the character model’s head clipping inside its torso (head located around the belly). The generated report instead talks about misaligned hand-to-weapon positioning, missing weapon textures, and lighting/shadow problems. It does not mention the character’s head or any torso clipping. Therefore, the two reports refer to different issues.","match":false}

{"reasoning":"Ground truth bug is about two cars intersecting: one floating and clipping into the other, i.e., physics/positioning issue with vehicles. Generated report talks about an unrelated issue: text overlay rendered incorrectly, breaking immersion. No mention of cars, floating, clipping, or positional overlap. Therefore they describe different bugs.","match":false}

{"reasoning":"Ground truth bug focuses on a weapon floating away from the character’s hand (hand in weapon-holding pose, weapon detached and clipping). The generated report instead talks about non-standard outfit, missing hands, and floating UI/text (“I Love Bacon”, “15.0”). It never mentions a weapon floating or clipping. Therefore, they do not describe the same issue.","match":false}

{"reasoning":"Ground truth bug is about two characters clipping/merging into each other. Generated report talks about clothing rendering, environment misalignment, and weapon obstruction but does not mention two characters intersecting. Issues described differ in focus and specifics.","match":false}

{"reasoning":"Ground truth: character is visibly inside (clipping through) the table. Generated report: says the character \"incorrectly colliding with the table, creating a gap between the character's body and the table surface,\" mentions translucent skin and missing hands – focuses on rendering/transparency issues, not the character intersecting the table geometry. It never states that the character is standing inside or clipping through the table; instead it describes a separation gap. Therefore, the two reports do not describe the same bug.","match":false}

{"reasoning":"The ground truth states that a character is clipping into terrain (rock), indicating a visual bug. The generated report explicitly claims there are no visual bugs or rendering issues. Therefore, the generated report does not describe the same bug and contradicts the ground truth.","match":false}

{"reasoning":"Ground truth bug is about a gun floating behind the character due to the holder not being rendered. Generated report talks about shadow misalignment and texture pop-in on character clothing. Issues described are entirely different; no mention of floating weapon or missing character render.","match":false}

{"reasoning":"Ground truth bug is about character clipping: a person is partially inside the brown horse, specifically the head intersecting the horse’s body. The generated report talks about the horse unrealistically standing on a flat surface in a desert and incorrect shadow alignment; it does not mention any character, clipping, or intersection between person and horse. Therefore the generated report does not describe the same issue.","match":false}

{"reasoning":"Ground truth bug concerns a combat vehicle whose model is largely missing, with only a few parts rendered. The generated report instead talks about a character model issue (helmet misaligned) and floating debris/weapon items. No mention of a combat vehicle or missing vehicle parts. The nature, affected asset, and symptoms differ completely.","match":false}
